	"such as lines and colors.  A collection\r\n"
	"is called $FG,GREEN$Sprite$FG$.\r\n\r\n"
	"You can create an icon by placing a picture\r\n"
	"with a payload of code to execute.\r\n"
	"This is a called a picture macro.\r\n"
	"Check \"Pop-Up\" for icons and \"Esc\" for\r\n"
	"cmd line macros.\r\n\r\n"
	"In a program, you first make a picture.\r\n"
	"Then, you insert a pointer to it.\r\n\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Insert just Picture (GrSprite)\",PT_PICTURE$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Picture Macro (Icon)\",PT_PICTURE_MACRO$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Picture Menu Item\",PT_PICTURE_MENU$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Picture Link\",PT_PICTURE_LINK$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Pointer to GrSprite Data\",PT_GRSPRITES_PTR$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"GrSprite Size (not really needed)\",PT_GRSPRITES_SIZE$\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Duplicate Picture\",PT_DUP_PICTURE$\r\n"
	"\r\n$MU,\"CANCEL\",LTFM_CANCEL$\r\n\r\n"
	"The potential exists for binary data\r\n"
	"besides $FG,GREEN$Sprites$FG$.  This is why\r\n"
	"the pointer to a Sprite is known as\r\n"
	"\"Insert Binary\".  There is one more\r\n"
	"option called \"Insert Binary Type\".\r\n"
	"The only other binary data type is source\r\n"
	"line info in map files.\r\n\r\n"
	"$MU,\"Insert Binary Data Type\",7$\r\n");
  i=PopUpMenu(l);
  LtfDel(l);
